SWINE FEVER, CLASSICAL - RUSSIA (SOUTHERN RUSSIA)
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
Date: 1 Sep 2000
From: Martin Hugh-Jones <mehj@mail.vetmed.lsu.edu>
Source: From various Russian sources, 21 - 25 Aug 2000

In Bashkiriya, Kiginskiy district, an outbreak of so-called "classic
plague" is reported. In the village of Bakiyarovo, 64 pigs caught it on the
Chkalov pig farm. Of the 64 that got sick, 18 died and were burned, 153
were slaughtered. Of the 1180 vaccinated, 708 were in the private sector.
The buildings housing the infected animals have been disinfected and a
quarantine enacted.
The team mobilized to liquidate the emergency included: the animal defense
team, a unit of the veterinary investigation, and 5 technical units
(equipment).
--
